[accomplishment]
title=Approved Ubuntu Member
description=You are an Approved Ubuntu Member
application=ubuntu-community
category=General
needs-signing=true
needs-information=launchpad-email
summary = An Ubuntu Member is someone who has demonstrated a <i>significant and sustained</i> contribution to Ubuntu. Each Ubuntu Member is seen as a reliable and dependable contributor to Ubuntu who has contributed to further and improve Ubunty. Importantly, Ubuntu Membership does not require any specific skill; great contributions in development, documentation, translations, advocacy, support, art, design, and many other areas are all worthy of membership.
steps: Contribute extensively to Ubuntu for a sustained period of time. There is no fixed time period, but this should be long enough to demonstrate your commitment to the project.
    Create a page on <tt>wiki.ubuntu.com</tt> that outlines your contributions. In the wiki page include your contributions, describe which teams you are in, and summarize your efforts.
    Ask your fellow community members to contribute testimonials of your contributions.
    Schedule yourself for review at a regional membership board meeting to review your contributions. You can find the nearest board using the links below.
links: http://wiki.ubuntu.com/Membership
	https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Membership/RegionalBoards
help = #ubuntu-community-team on Freenode
